Item ID5293

Tarromin seeds can be planted in a herb patch with level 19 Farming in order to produce grimy tarromins. It can be obtained from monsters or as an uncommon loot from pickpocketing Master Farmers.

Note: A nearby gardener will not watch over your growing herb.

Changes[edit | edit source]

Date Changes
23 July 2020
(update | poll)

The appearance of herbs planted in herb patches now match the herb's appearance in the player's inventory.

9 January 2020
(update | poll)

Players can now dig up healthy herb patches before they're fully grown. To prevent players from gaining experience repeatedly by planting and digging up herb seeds, the experience usually gained from planting them are now given when harvesting them, alongside the usual harvesting experience.

8 February 2018
(update | poll)

The value was changed from 7 to 3 so that it would appear below less valuable seeds when on the ground.

11 July 2005
(update)
  • The item was renamed from "Herb seed" to "Tarromin seed".
  • The item's examine was changed from "Farming skill coming in July!" to "A tarromin seed - plant in a herb patch."
